      "source": [
        "# Bootstrap para estimar la media de tiempos de entrega\n",
        "\n",
        "En este notebook se aplica el método Bootstrap a una muestra de 12 tiempos de entrega.\n",
        "\n",
        "El objetivo es:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Usar la muestra original.\n",
        "2. Generar 1000 muestras Bootstrap con reemplazo.\n",
        "3. Calcular la media de cada muestra Bootstrap.\n",
        "4. Obtener la media Bootstrap.\n",
        "5. Calcular la desviación estándar Bootstrap.\n",
        "6. Calcular los percentiles 2.5% y 97.5%.\n",
        "7. Construir un intervalo de confianza Bootstrap al 95%."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 37,
      "id": "59e8f5bc",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "59e8f5bc"
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "source": [
        "# Importamos las librerías necesarias\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "f8c9f561",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "f8c9f561"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 1. Definición de la muestra original\n",
        "\n",
        "La muestra contiene 12 tiempos de entrega."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 38,
      "id": "9523234d",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "9523234d",
        "outputId": "c48b9c62-a0e4-46c9-e639-53509dfee050"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Muestra original:\n",
            "[35 42 38 40 45 37 39 41 44 36 43 40]\n",
            "\n",
            "Tamaño de la muestra:\n",
            "12\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Esta es la muestra aleatoria de 12 tiempos de entrega que aparece en el pizarrón\n",
        "datos = np.array([35, 42, 38, 40, 45, 37, 39, 41, 44, 36, 43, 40])\n",
        "\n",
        "# Guardamos el tamaño de la muestra original\n",
        "# En este caso n = 12\n",
        "n = len(datos)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Mostramos la muestra original\n",
        "print('Muestra original:')\n",
        "print(datos)\n",
        "\n",
        "print('\\nTamaño de la muestra:')\n",
        "print(n)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "cf4b14d1",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "cf4b14d1"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 2. Media de la muestra original\n",
        "\n",
        "Calculamos la media muestral de los 12 tiempos de entrega."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 39,
      "id": "2f4fd12a",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "2f4fd12a",
        "outputId": "e0393867-b75f-4de5-8a91-0f9670b6c977"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Media de la muestra original:\n",
            "40.0\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# La media muestral es el promedio de los 12 tiempos de entrega\n",
        "media_original = np.mean(datos)\n",
        "\n",
        "print('Media de la muestra original:')\n",
        "print(media_original)"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "df6ec981",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "df6ec981"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 3. Generación de muestras Bootstrap\n",
        "\n",
        "Una muestra Bootstrap se obtiene tomando datos de la muestra original con reemplazo.\n",
        "\n",
        "Esto significa que un mismo valor puede aparecer más de una vez en una misma muestra Bootstrap."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 40,
      "id": "ec5ea642",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "ec5ea642",
        "outputId": "cfe14a09-71e2-4001-c47c-ed34642d974a"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Primeras 5 muestras bootstrap:\n",
            "[[39 36 40 40 35 37 36 36 35 42 39 42]\n",
            " [37 37 36 36 39 42 41 36 44 36 41 41]\n",
            " [40 40 41 40 35 45 36 42 38 35 36 44]\n",
            " [40 43 38 39 44 36 42 40 35 41 44 37]\n",
            " [38 37 40 36 35 37 35 39 39 36 41 35]]\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Número de muestras bootstrap que queremos generar\n",
        "B = 1000\n",
        "\n",
        "# Creamos un generador aleatorio\n",
        "rng = np.random.default_rng()\n",
        "\n",
        "muestras_bootstrap = rng.choice(\n",
        "    datos,          # datos originales de donde vamos a remuestrear\n",
        "    size=(B, n),    # 1000 muestras, cada una de tamaño 12\n",
        "    replace=True    # muestreo con reemplazo\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Mostramos las primeras 5 muestras bootstrap\n",
        "print('Primeras 5 muestras bootstrap:')\n",
        "print(muestras_bootstrap[:5])"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "5c0fe72d",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "5c0fe72d"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 4. Media de cada muestra Bootstrap\n",
        "\n",
        "Ahora calculamos el promedio de cada una de las 1000 muestras Bootstrap."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": 41,
      "id": "cb0157d3",
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "cb0157d3",
        "outputId": "870e2a07-00b3-40ed-e72c-7c52c49880d5"
      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Primeras 10 medias bootstrap:\n",
            "[38.08333333 38.83333333 39.33333333 39.91666667 37.33333333 40.5\n",
            " 39.66666667 40.         39.16666667 40.91666667]\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "# Para cada una de las 1000 muestras bootstrap calculamos su media\n",
        "medias_bootstrap = np.mean(muestras_bootstrap, axis=1)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Mostramos las primeras 10 medias bootstrap\n",
        "print('Primeras 10 medias bootstrap:')\n",
        "print(medias_bootstrap[:10])"
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "id": "213c2c81",
      "metadata": {
        "id": "213c2c81"
      },
      "source": [
        "## 5. Media de las medias Bootstrap\n",
        "\n",
        "Esta cantidad resume el promedio de todas las medias obtenidas por Bootstrap."
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
